The Experimental Forest, encompassing 6,865 acres in the Idaho City, Idaho area, was established to make permanently available an area for silvicultural and other related research in the ponderosa pine type.  Timber cutting is limited to that necessary for research studies or to provide areas suitable for future research programs.  Research in the Experimental Forest began in 1933.</abstract><purpose>This dataset was designed to be used for map display, and analysis in future Forest Plan Revisions. These data should be displayed and analyzed at scales appropriate for 1:24,000-scale data - it is believed that this layer was digitized from 1:24000 maps, most likely mylar.
